description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a substantive or fixed term Consultant Medical Oncologist at Yeovil District Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. The successful candidate will join a friendly, enthusiastic and innovative team, working with two other Medical Oncologists who together with visiting Consultant colleagues from neighbouring Musgrove Park Hospital in Taunton, will work with an exceptional team of nurses and allied health professionals to deliver the very best care to our community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a full time (10 PA) candidate to provide Oncology services in at least 3 tumour sites, including 2.5 SPA within the job plan for personal and professional development. The role will include provision of outpatient clinics, attendance at relevant MDTs and Acute Oncology ward rounds. We are looking in particular for someone with specialty interests in Lung, Urology, Upper GI, Gynaecology, Breast or leadership of the well-established Acute Oncology Service (attracting 1 PA within the job plan) and 3 ward rounds per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yeovil District Hospital NHS Foundation Trust participates in a wide number of research and clinical trials, and the successful candidate will have plenty of opportunities to further their research interest. There will be no on-call commitment, as out of hours advice is provided by on-call Consultant colleagues in Taunton. The post-holder will experience significant professional and governance peer support from The Beacon Centre at Musgrove Park Hospital enjoying all the benefits of close working with our nearby regional cancer centre, including joint Consultant meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yeovil District Hospital&#39;s Oncology Unit is CHKS accredited and has enjoyed a stable and successful history; trusted and respected by our patients, staff and commissioners. We have been repeatedly rated as one of the top-10 healthcare employers in the country, a leading light in global stroke research and development, and attracted national interest in our iCARE model, which has established the principles of exemplary patient care experience within our hospital. Yeovil District Hospital NHS consistently performs well in the National Patient Experience Survey for Cancer Services. There are many opportunities for the successful candidate to develop services further, based on personal interest and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yeovil District Hospital is a modern hospital in pleasant countryside only two hours from London, close to the Dorset border and less than one hour from both the Jurassic and North Devon coasts. There are excellent facilities in a purpose built Education Centre on-site and state of the art MDT meeting facilities. Substantial parking is available on-site in a new multi-story car park. Yeovil District Hospital is identified us as one of the most innovative trusts in the country giving us unique access to national support and funding to realise our exciting plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consideration will be given to candidates wishing to work part-time and job share opportunities would also be considered. The trust prides itself on its flexible and supportive ethos promoting staff wellbeing and a healthy work/life balance in this beautiful part of the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have MBBS and MRCP qualifications or equivalent and be fully registered with the GMC and hold a licence to practise. Applicants must have entry on the GMC Specialist Register for Medical or Clinical Oncology via CCT (proposed CCT date must be within six months of the interview date), CESR or European Community Rights. Consideration will be given to candidates without entry on the GMC Specialist Register on a fixed term basis providing relevant experience at consultant level. Support will be provided to Candidates to achieve CSER).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We really value the impact that you as a Consultant will have on our patients and services; we therefore offer an enhanced benefits package (subject to criteria) which includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Welcome to Yeovil payment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A generous relocation package, including Visa and travel costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10 hours of paid time for professional development every week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£700 personal budget for training and development every year.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love to discuss the opportunities available to you further, so to arrange an informal visit, or to ask any questions, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caroline Osborne, Clinical Director for Cancer Services, by emailing Caroline.Osborne@ydh.nhs.uk or Luke Curtis, Manager for Cancer Services, by emailing Luke.Curtis@ydh.nhs.uk or telephoning 01935 606726.&lt;/p&gt;
